\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 # HarborGuard AI - Product Requirements Document (PRD)\cf2 \strokec4 \
\
**Version:** 1.0  \
**Date:** March 2025  \
**Status:** MVP Development  \
**Target:** Single coding agent or small dev team  \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec5 ---\cf2 \strokec4 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec3 ## 1. Document Purpose\cf2 \strokec4 \
\
This PRD provides exhaustive technical specifications for building HarborGuard AI, a maritime supply chain disruption decision-support platform. Every section contains actionable implementation details including exact data structures, API contracts, algorithmic logic, and UI specifications.\
\
**After reading this document, a coding agent should be able to:**\
\cf2 \strokec3 -\cf2 \strokec4  Generate complete database schemas\
\cf2 \strokec3 -\cf2 \strokec4  Implement all backend API endpoints\
\cf2 \strokec3 -\cf2 \strokec4  Build frontend components with exact props and state management\
\cf2 \strokec3 -\cf2 \strokec4  Configure third-party integrations (Gemini API)\
\cf2 \strokec3 -\cf2 \strokec4  Deploy the application using Docker\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec5 ---\cf2 \strokec4 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec3 ## 2. Product Overview\cf2 \strokec4 \
\
\cf2 \strokec3 ### 2.1 Problem Statement\cf2 \strokec4 \
Mid-market electronics manufacturers ($100M-$300M revenue) lose 10-15% of annual revenue to preventable supply chain disruptions. When port disruptions occur, supply chain teams manually scramble across ERP dashboards, spreadsheets, and email threads. By the time decisions are made, millions in revenue are already at risk.\
\
\cf2 \strokec3 ### 2.2 Solution\cf2 \strokec4 \
HarborGuard AI is a decision-support web application that:\
\cf2 \strokec3 1.\cf2 \strokec4  Detects maritime disruption events (starting with manual input, mock data for MVP)\
\cf2 \strokec3 2.\cf2 \strokec4  Automatically calculates financial exposure across inventory SKUs\
\cf2 \strokec3 3.\cf2 \strokec4  Simulates 4 predefined mitigation strategies with full financial modeling\
\cf2 \strokec3 4.\cf2 \strokec4  Recommends optimal strategy based on company-specific "Risk DNA" parameters\
\cf2 \strokec3 5.\cf2 \strokec4  Generates actionable execution drafts (supplier emails, logistics requests, executive memos) via LLM\
\
\cf2 \strokec3 ### 2.3 Core Value Proposition\cf2 \strokec4 \
Transform a 12-hour manual decision process into a 2-minute AI-assisted workflow that preserves millions in revenue.\
\
\cf2 \strokec3 ### 2.4 Target User\cf2 \strokec4 \
**Primary:** VP of Supply Chain at mid-market US electronics manufacturer  \
**Secondary:** COO, CFO (economic sign-off)\
\
\cf2 \strokec3 ### 2.5 Demo Scenario (MVP Focus)\cf2 \strokec4 \
**Event:** Labor strike at Port of Los Angeles  \
**Impact:** 12-day delay, 35% capacity reduction  \
**Exposure:** 47 containers, 18 high-priority SKUs, $38.4M revenue at risk  \
**Optimal Strategy:** Split (60% reroute to Oakland, 20% air freight, 20% buffer stock)  \
**Result:** $9.5M net financial impact preserved\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
